I changed the transformers so the interface will be simpler and cleaner, and to allow future improvements.

> I'm bothered by the fact that a function rule will delete the tree
It won't delete the tree, that's what InPlace means..

But yes, you can still get the tree, it's just not the default anymore.

Do:
```python
class MyTransformer(Transformer_InPlace):
    @v_args(tree=True)
    def some_rule(self, tree: Tree):
        tree.children = [...]
        return tree
```
Or
```python
@v_args(tree=True)
class MyTransformer(Transformer_InPlace):
    def some_rule(self, tree: Tree):
        tree.children = [...]
        return tree
```
